{
  "stem": "9091.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Moshe-- M-O-S-H-E-- Rojek-- R-O-J-E-K.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born in 13 of July in 1933.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Warsaw, Poland.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Since I was six years old, so there are not that many things that I remember from before the war till 1939.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But there are a few things that I-- that I remember.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I-- I remember, for instance, my father wasn't religious, even so his father was.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he didn't know his father, since his father died when he was about four years old.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And by the way, he grew up in Janusz Korczak's orphanage.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So over there, he didn't get really a religious upraising.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he wasn't religious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in his ideology, he was leftist.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and he-- in our house, religion wasn't really a factor, except that we lived with our grandmother, which-- What was her name?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her name was Chaya.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was my father's mother, and she was very religious.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she tried to introduce some religion to me, which, in later years, had quite a significance [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] because she tried to send me-- on our block where we lived, there was a synagogue with a heder, which is a place where you send children in very young age, about 5 or so, to study Hebrew and prayers and so on.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So she secretly, without my father's knowledge, used to send me there to study Hebrew reading and prayers.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And also, when she would feed me, she would make sure that I put a kippah and make the prayers before the eating.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's a story.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I must have been somewhere around four-- between four and five years old-- around five years old maybe, which I guess that's one of the earliest memories of mine.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
